<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,804,891]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,973,804,828]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis. –</emphasis>
Paramere apico-medially and subbasally each with 1 distinct incision (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1207,836,859]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); surstylus with dense, irregular scale-shaped processes basally (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1365,868,891]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,932,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,986,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Description. –</emphasis>
Thorax: Mesonotum submedially and laterally with black longitudinal stripes, 2 per side; submedial stripes converge on prescutum. Pleura with 2 long, longitudinal
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" startId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" targetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1476,2035,2114]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 11-14. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Wang, 2004" authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2004" box="[254,558,2035,2056]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trisetosa" status="new species" subGenus="Oxyphortica">
<emphasis box="[254,558,2035,2056]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[570,685,2035,2056]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,752,193,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">stripes: one of them below wing, the other from fore coxa to metapleura.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,753,289,344]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Wing: Dark brown, yellow along posterior margin. Halter: stalk grey; apical part white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,753,385,408]" box="[113,753,385,408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Legs: Mid tibia basally with 3 long, strong posterodorsal setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,752,449,504]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Abdominal tergites yellow, black along lateral and posterior margins. Sternites black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,752,545,728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
Male terminalia: Epandrium constricted mid-dorsally, with 1 row of long, strong setae and several short setae along posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[310,391,609,632]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Paramere inter-subbasally with serrated process (
<figureCitation box="[319,407,641,664]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), medially with 1 sclerotized projection (
<figureCitation box="[241,323,673,696]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically broadly separated (
<figureCitation box="[121,203,705,728]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2035,2056]" captionTargetBox="[143,1466,1092,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-370@4.[116,1485,1057,2002]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 11-14. Stegana (Oxyphortica) trisetosa, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618905/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,752,769,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
