<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1452,527,683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,940,527,551]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Remarks. –</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<emphasis box="[1211,1224,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2004" box="[1241,1379,527,550]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prigenti" subGenus="Oxyphortica">
(
<emphasis box="[1250,1269,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">O</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1294,1379,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">prigenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the many characters, but can be clearly distinguished from the latter by apico-medially and subbasally each with 1 distinct incision and surstylus with dense, irregular scale-shaped processes basally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
